 the\n21st century. The variability is partially due to the different implementations\nof aerosol forcings in the models. The assessment of the pole wards shifts of\ndry zones in climate simulations show that the multi-model means of the two\nsubsets of leaking and flooding models produce spatial shifts similar in size\nas expected from 21st century global warming simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Sep 2011 21:56:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-09-30"}
